Description: CONCEPT: The EU metro regions are NUTS 3 regions or groupings of NUTS 3 regions used as approximations of all agglomerations of at least 250 000 inhabitants. The selection of the NUTS 3 components of the metro regions is based on the definition of Functional urban areas (FUAs). These FUAs contain the major cities and their surrounding commuter belts.
Non-metropolitan regions in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia
